  "texts": [
    "Ricci flow coupled with harmonic map flow), see [Mül12].",
    "It was shown in [Wil15, Prop.",
    "2.10], based in turn on Hamilton's analogous Ricci flow result, that for a closed source manifold, expanding gradient solitons must be harmonic-Einstein.",
    "The only difference for us is that our source B is non-compact.",
    "However, due to the equivariance of gB and h, and the fact that B is compact, the same proof works."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}